Package org.botblock.javabotblockapi.requests

Interface GetBotAction

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    GetBotActionImpl
    public interface GetBotAction
    Interface used to perform various GET actions towards the /api/bots/:id endpoint.

    All GET requests are cached for 2 minutes, to prevent rate limits.

    • Method Detail

      • getBotInfo

        JSONObject getBotInfo​(@NotNull
                      @NotNull Long id)
        Gives the complete bot info returned by BotBlock.

        The returned JSONObject may look like this: 

        
 {
     "id": "123456789012345678",
     "username": "MyBot",
     "discriminator": "1234",
     "owners": [
         "234567890123456789"
     ],
     "server_count": 100,
     "invite": "https://discordapp.com/oauth2/authorize?client_id=123456789012345678&scope=bot",
     "prefix": "?",
     "website": "",
     "github": "",
     "support": "",
     "library": "JDA",
     "list_data": {
         "somebotlist.com": [
             {"data": "Unique bot list data"},
             200
         ],
         "otherlist.org": [
             {"data": "Unique bot list data"},
             404
         ]
     }
 }

        With exception of id and list_data are all shown values based on the most common appearance of it.
        The information returned in list_data is unique per bot list.
        Parameters:
        id - The bot id to get information from.
        Returns:
        JSONObject containing the bot information.

      • getDiscriminator

        String getDiscriminator​(@NotNull
                        @NotNull Long id)
        Gives the discriminator of the bot.
        The discriminator is the for digit number in a Tag (example: MyBot#1234).
        Parameters:
        id - The id of the bot to get the discriminator from.
        Returns:
        String containing the discriminator, or 0000 when the provided id is invalid.
        Since:
        4.2.0
